<task id="020" project="ai-procedure-quality-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit skills batch 1 (skills 1–6 alphabetically)</title>
    <phase>2a</phase>
    <stream>audit</stream>
    <tags>audit, skills, parallel-batch</tags>
    <estimate>30min</estimate>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <parallel-group>2a-W1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>001, 011</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Audit 6 skills against the 7 best practices PLUS the Light reference check from F-15.3. Return findings as structured output; do NOT modify any skill files. Main session writes per-batch findings to notes/audit/batch-1.md.</goal>
    <context>This batch covers the first 6 skills alphabetically from the inventory produced by task 001. Sub-agents are read-only on .claude/; they return findings, main session writes them out.</context>
    <constraints>
      - READ ONLY on .claude/skills/. NO writes to skill files.
      - Output to projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/audit/batch-1.md (not into .claude/)
      - Apply the 7 best practices from spec.md verbatim
      - **Tiered line-count target (F-15.1)**: SKILL.md body ≤200 lines is the goal; ≤400 lines is the cap with justification; over 400 lines MUST split.
      - **Light reference check (F-15.3 mandatory)**: every file path resolves, every URL resolves, every referenced skill exists. Record results per skill.
      - **Medium reference check (F-15.3 recommended for ops-heavy skills)**: for any skill that prescribes commands or contains code examples, spot-check whether the commands are still valid syntax and code patterns match current state at the referenced location. If too expensive to do thoroughly, flag the skill `needs-substantive-rewrite` for a focused follow-up.
      - For each skill, recommend `exemplar:` value: a real path OR `none-too-volatile` with rationale
      - Recommended action options: `refine-in-place` / `split` / `merge-with-X` / `remove` / `leave-alone` / `leave-alone-justified` (over-target but warranted) / `needs-substantive-rewrite` (structure OK, content needs focused session)
      - Honesty: if a skill is already in good shape, say so. Do not fabricate problems.
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/inventory/skills.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/inventory/skill-cross-refs.json</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/_template/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read notes/inventory/skills.md and skill-cross-refs.json; identify skills 1–6 alphabetically</step>
    <step>For each skill, read its SKILL.md plus any subdirectory content</step>
    <step>**Structural assessment**: description-quality, body-line-count vs tiered target (F-15.1), goal-vs-prescriptive, gotchas-section, overlap-with-other-skills, deterministic-rules-to-extract</step>
    <step>**Light reference check (mandatory)**: for each file path the skill mentions, Test-Path. For each URL, HEAD (warn-only on 4xx/5xx). For each referenced skill, verify it exists in skill-cross-refs.json. Record `references-verified: pass/fail/notes`.</step>
    <step>**Medium reference check (where applicable)**: if the skill prescribes commands (build, deploy, refactor steps), do a syntactic sanity check — does the command syntax still match the tool's current CLI? If the skill embeds code examples, do they match the current code at the referenced location? If thorough Medium check would exceed ~10min, flag the skill `needs-substantive-rewrite` and STOP the Medium pass for that skill.</step>
    <step>**Cross-reference impact** (for any skill considered for split/merge/remove): cite from skill-cross-refs.json who currently references this skill. The refinement (Phase 2b) MUST update all of them.</step>
    <step>**Exemplar recommendation**: real path OR `none-too-volatile` with rationale (per F-15)</step>
    <step>**Recommended action**: refine-in-place / split / merge-with-X / remove / leave-alone / leave-alone-justified / needs-substantive-rewrite</step>
    <step>Write projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/audit/batch-1.md with one section per skill containing all fields above</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output>projects/ai-procedure-quality-r1/notes/audit/batch-1.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 6 skills assessed against all 7 best practices</criterion>
    <criterion>Tiered line-count tier (PASS / OVER-TARGET-justified / SPLIT-required) recorded per skill</criterion>
    <criterion>Light reference check completed for every skill; results recorded as references-verified: pass/fail/notes</criterion>
    <criterion>Medium reference check attempted for ops-heavy skills; skills flagged `needs-substantive-rewrite` where Medium check was too expensive</criterion>
    <criterion>For any skill considered for split/merge/remove: cross-reference impact section cites callers from skill-cross-refs.json</criterion>
    <criterion>Each skill has a recommended action (one of 7: refine-in-place / split / merge / remove / leave-alone / leave-alone-justified / needs-substantive-rewrite)</criterion>
    <criterion>Each skill has a recommended `exemplar:` value</criterion>
    <criterion>No .claude/ files modified</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
